<rss xmlns:taxo="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/taxonomy/" xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" version="2.0">
  <channel>
    <title>Tank balance</title>
    <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=20156</link>
    <description>&lt;DIV&gt;I was reading through more posts, seeing more disinformation and junk as always in this forum, and so decided to lay out what I think is the real problem here. People are b**ching and moaning and claiming class X is superior, and we get hyperbole like "knights out-tank warriors" (which is not true anyway, healing&amp;nbsp;is not equal to tanking, period, else people would be suggesting to people on the low end to only go for hp augs instead of ac augs) or all these stupid inane comparisons of tank class aggro (newsflash, our aggro is irrelevant to each other, its only next to the people we need to keep aggro over that matters, as I don't think anyone is going to complain they can't keep aggro over the other tank classes if the other tank class isn't trying to get aggro).&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Look, when I think about building a group for something, I have always looked at it this way:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1) Warriors - needed for the heaviest encounters&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2) Paladins - needed for group heals and backup rez&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3) SKs - needed for pulling&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;That's the only distinction I, and anyone I have ever played with has made when choosing tanks (and lets be honest here, 9/10 times people are taking whatever tank in their GUILD that is available or sends them a tell first, not any particular kind).&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The problem isn't the fact that the "tanking gap has been closed", the problem is that we have&amp;nbsp;not had CHALLENGING CONTENT for anyone that has even Plane of Time or Qvic level equipment (yeah, a few things may be a little challenging at that level, but seriously, the fact that its debatable at all is ridiculous).&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Is the tanking gap closed? Do monks and rangers tank as well as us? They certainly seem to tank all the time in exp groups now. I don't think so. I think the gimp content has led to bunching all of us up at the top because we all have such high ac, have so many avoidance and mitigation aa, that the absolute scale of differences in how we tank means the differences are trivial.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I mean, seriously, if you have anguish gear, there is little reason for a knight to "need" to use a shield and shield block unless their 1h/2h weapon difference dictates it. Yeah, many use the 1h/shield because of all the ac and magelo padding, but seriously, from an efficiency standpoint knights should be using their 2.0/2,5 epics&amp;nbsp;99.9% of the time.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;You can talk about "closing the gap" all you want, but the fact of the matter is, guilds are not having knights main tank any serious raid bosses, regardless of how much more hp/ac they have (and with a shield equipped). because raid bosses are not gimp experience mobs, and they will splat knights, and I am not talking wholly about under defensive either. When we are light on warriors, I have been asked to tank in low end places like tacvi before (3400+ ac) and I still go splat 1/2 the time. Is it all DI(-1)? It shouldn't be, I don't know, but our warriors with 500 less ac than me and only a little more hp than me never seem to go splat at near that rate unless we are wiping to something.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I wish SoE would implement some serious single group challenging content with high exp yields and drops even raiders would want (augs and clickies if that's the only way they can justify useful items, or just put in some freaking occasional 350+ hp items for one slot per class or class/type as random zone wide drops maybe) that were not balanced for your average group, but were balanced for your freaking high end raiders.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Remember when GoD was new? And even people that had been in Time for a year before GoD came out wanted to do ikki trials and group in KT for augs and items? And it was hard. It was barely doable for those with lesser gear, but it was doable. People took warriors for groups that were camping named because they hit freaking hard (many of those named still hit harder than 90 of single group content that has come out since). They took paladins for backup rez and heals, they took sks for pulling. And knights *could* tank that stuff if they were geared up enough. I personally thought that was how it should be (if anyone can think of some other  make sks more desired, I'm all for it, I have always thought they got the short end of the stick outside of soloing, and soloing now isn't even that great for them like it used to be).&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Right now, I feel like instead of the above, this is what people do when looking for a tank:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1) Warrior - generic group&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2) Paladin - fighting undead, heals&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3) SK - can't find a puller&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;99% of content doesn't require a "puller" anymore. It just doesn't. And the content that really does, an SK is a poor choice particularly if they are the tank. Though maybe it doesn't matter when the ranger can tank the gimp content. Paladins had it good for a few months when people were camping illsilan and those undead DoD missions, but that advantage is fading quick as people move into new expansions with little undead. With no serious need for a defensive warrior, and no need for a puller specifically in most cases, I know I'd want a paladin (personally, I may be biased being one, and being more defensive oriented so I like having back up healers) due simply to the group heals, nothing else.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;So I guess my question is, should we be asking for SoE to introduce some freaking challenging content (and yes, that means some people can't do it until they get equipped for it), or should we be asking for group-favorable abilities that make warriors, and sks to a lesser extent, preferred in certain content or in certain group class makeups?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I personally wish SoE would just add some seriously hard and rewarding content so that the actual differences in classes matters again and becomes apparent.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I know many want more gimmicks and more class "parity" in&amp;nbsp;non-tanking abilities though, so what do YOU (person reading this) want?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I'm not talking about taunt changes or aggro or endurance regen or itemization. Those problems are irrelevant to TANK balance, they are game mechanics problems that need fixes regardless. But so many people are complaining about tank balance in the group game, I'd like to know what people really want. Better content that scales to the differing abilities of classes, or more "parity" in non-tanking junk so that there is no difference between tanks at all.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
    <pubDate>Thu, 25 May 2006 17:19:17 GMT</pubDate>
