      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=20786#M20786</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;A weapon's quality is more than just its ratio.&amp;nbsp; The actual damage and actual delay plays a part.&amp;nbsp; Primary, Secondary and Tertiary stats all play a part.&amp;nbsp; For example a 9/19 6STR 6STA sword is theoretically of higher quality than a 13/26 no-stat sword.&amp;nbsp; Further, a 25/40 sword eventually loses out to the 9/19 sword at about level 48 if I recall.&amp;nbsp; That's why I don't object to swords like the GSoM, they may have similar ratios, but they're not in the same league as 2.0s for pure quality.</description>
