    <item>
      <title>Re: Tank balance</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=20729#M20729</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Why shouldn't knights tank like warriors? They are warriors, spell casting warriors. Trying to make "hybrid" classes was silly anyway. Paladins aren't half warrior/ half cleric. That was a dumb notion to begin with, they are Paladins. Holy warriors who are granted spells by their diety as recompense for thier service. The paper game is pretty straight forward.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Paladin has same thaco, same attacks, same hitdice, same con bounus, same armor bonus, same armor types. The only difference is that warriors get weapon spec and paladins get spells, that's the basic crux of it. That and warriors get more feats than paladins do, but the spells balance it out really well and at epic levels they have all the feats they would need anyhow. Paladins are indeed tanks, very powerful tanks. The Blackguards are so evil that they give a neg 2 modifier to any one around them that can't be resisted.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;You can state the differences between EQ and D and D all day, but they are far more closely related than some of you want to admit. Knights are seriously closer to thier paper cousins than they have ever been.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;Paladin is a warrior class that favors good alignments with dietic favors,&amp;nbsp;Shadowknight is a warrior class that favors evil. Rangers are a warrior class based on druidic lore. Plain ol warriors are just that, plain ol generic warriors, dime a dozen. When one falls 10 takes thier place, cannon fodder, arrow catchers, groundpounders, grunts, jarheads, leathernecks.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Knights and rangers are basically prestige classes of warrior.&amp;nbsp;They are tank pluses because they are in fact warrior pluses.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
