terrupting capability of bash.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Apples or oranges, not ignorance. IF Warriors are to be "freed" from random aggro events as a developer stated when defending the entirely inappropriate Swiftcleave as our long anticipated real mainhand upgrade, then I expect procs like Lure of Ice, not another half-spatchedcocked retread of the venerable Y'Kesha proc with a new name and the same tired old doesn't stun and the pathectic DD doesn't stick.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Revision of offensive and defensive disciplines to give Warriors an offensive and defensive "stance" when used in combination with appropriate weapons, augments, and weapon buffs.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;And no more nonsence like WoT/DS that further enhances Knight downward scaling and soloing capability. They have nearly double the capability of Warirors right now versus all but the most difficult content.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;These things aren't asking for godmode. They aren't even really asking for great Warrior superiority vs the hardest group content (if a top of the line &lt;u&gt;non-raiding&lt;/u&gt; Wariror can handle it, lower progression &lt;u&gt;raid&lt;/u&gt; Knights have 0 legitimate complaint). It's asking for a bone - an end to Warrior class neglect and stagnation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
