      <description>I won't pretend to know implimentation details, BUT.....&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Such a system does not have to be as complicated as Call of Challange, an ability that has a chance of working if the mobs is fleeing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;All that "needs" to happen is a "Special Openings" random spin every combat round that an opening is not currently active. For example intOpening=getRandom(100)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;if(intOpening&amp;gt;10 &amp;amp;&amp;amp; intOpening&amp;lt;15) then {&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; if (vulnerableTo ThisKindof Attack(mob[Targeted]) == TRUE) {&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; plyrOpening=constSlice&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; tmrOpening=constTwoSeconds&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; ungray(btnSlice)&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; displayMessage("You see an opprotunity to cut ", mobName[mob[Targeted]], "'s", bodyPart[getRandom(constNbrOfBodyParts)]&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; }&lt;br&gt;}&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Overly simplified no doubt, but there need not be any mob attribute beyond vulnerability and nothing in the mob AI whatsoever. The &lt;u&gt;appearance&lt;/u&gt; that mobs "create" vulnerabilities doesn't require that they actually create them.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;It's kinda like WoW's Rage system in that the burden is all in the player's methods and attributes, not necessarily the mob's.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
